<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-06-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-06-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="263" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-06-09"><hi rend="italic">June 9,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 453.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to the Department’s instruction
                            No. 411, of March 25, 1898, which was received here on April 9 last, I
                            have the honor to state that the embassy has to-day been informed by the
                            foreign office that there are no Imperial regulations forbidding the use
                            of the German national flag for advertising purposes (zu Anzeigezwecken
                            im Handelsund Geschaftsverkehr).</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">And. D. White.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>